					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-405561#post-1840898</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-405561/scp-1891#post-1840898</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 27 Aug 2013 16:23:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MerleBlues</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1705585</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Very interesting. I wonder, why just paintings? Do they have to be on canvas, or can it modify any image produced via paints/pigments?</p> <p>What happens if you put an image that's already mostly machines - say, a painting of a car in a garage - in proximity? Does this SCP take the original machine's purpose into account?</p> <p>I also have to wonder what might happen if an image were altered by a human subject while the SCP was at work - say, painting over its work, or attempting to assist.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
